		<description><![CDATA[Now Buy Dell XPS One 27 &#8211; Dell launched their largest ever 27 inch all-in-one computer in the market today as part of the premium...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.quickonlinetips.com/" rel="nofollow">Home</a> &gt; <a href="http://www.quickonlinetips.com/archives/category/computers/" title="View all posts in Computers" rel="category tag">Computers</a></p><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://www.quickonlinetips.com/archives/2012/05/dell-xps-one-27-largest-all-in-one-dell-computer/&t=Buy Dell XPS One 27: Largest All-in-One Dell Computer" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.quickonlinetips.com/media/rss/fbshare.png" border="0" alt="Facebook Share"></a>&nbsp;<a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Buy Dell XPS One 27: Largest All-in-One Dell Computer - http://www.quickonlinetips.com/archives/?p=26627 via @qot" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.quickonlinetips.com/media/rss/tweetit.png" border="0" alt="Twitter Share"></a><p>Now Buy <strong>Dell XPS One 27</strong> &#8211; Dell launched their largest ever 27 inch all-in-one computer in the market today as part of the premium XPS performance family. Dell has also <a href="http://content.dell.com/us/en/corp/d/secure/2012-05-29-dell-consumer-all-in-one-computer.aspx" target="_blank">launched</a> a new series of all-in-one computers with different screen sizes ranging from 20 to 27 inches.</p>
<p>The <a href="http://www.apple.com/imac/" target="_blank">Apple iMac</a> has been available in 27 inch all-in-one size for many years now. The <a href="http://www.apple.com/displays/" target="_blank">Apple 27 inch display</a> is also around for a long time. As consumers continue to demand large screen experiences on their computers, PC manufacturers are now gearing up to provide the all-in-one solution on Windows-based systems.</p>
<h3>Dell XPS One 27</h3>
<p><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-26628" title="dell-xps-one-27" src="http://www.quickonlinetips.com/archives/wp-content/uploads/dell-xps-one-27.jpg" alt="dell xps one 27 computer" width="250" height="246" />The new <a href="http://content.dell.com/us/en/home/d/campaigns/xps-one-27.aspx" target="_blank">XPS one 27</a> claims have one of the most vibrant display screens ever created by Dell, with a stunning 2560&#215;1440 full quad HD clarity with a 16:9 WLED display. The new computer will feature high performance graphics from NVIDIA with entertainment features like Waves MaxxAudio 4 and Infinity-branded speakers.</p>
<p>It is powered by a full HD web cam, dual digital microphone, integrated 7.1 surround sound, USB 3.0 ports, integrated Wi-Fi, integrated Bluetooth, integrated ethernet, HDMI ports, slot loading DVD writer, and 8-in-1 media card reader. It also boasts of some cool optional features like slot loading Blu-ray disk drive and an internal TV tuner card.</p>
<p>The<strong> Dell XPS one 27</strong> is powered by a third generation Intel quad core processors with Intel Turbo boost technology and promises superfast computing with Windows 7 premium, speedy start-up and quick data transfer. It can be configured with up to 2 TB hard disk, up to 16 GB of DDR3 RAM,  optional NVIDIA GeForce GT 640M 2GB DDR5 graphics card, with optional HDD + 32GB mSATA SSD and Intel Smart Response Technology.</p>
<p>These new all in one computers are getting popular because they are space-saving, have a single power cord, and are useful with a wireless keyboard and mouse. With built-in Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, speakers, web camera, USB 3.0 ports, ethernet, and the whole processor built behind the LED screen &#8211; this is clutter free and what the future will be for all computers. It was high time that PC manufacturers got active in the 27 inch display space, which iMac has been ruling for a long time.</p>
<p>Dell XPS One 27 is now available for sale in select countries in Asia, at a starting price of $1399 only. (Compare that to the starting price of a 27 inch Apple iMac from $1699).</p>
